<span class="headers">Coldain Insignia Ring Quests </span>
<p>
<h4>(<i>Tradeskill portion only</i>)</h4> 
<p>
This is only the tradeskill portion of the first and third coldain insignia rings. More complete writeups for the quests can be found at:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/quest/garadainsrings.html" target="_new">Garadain's Rings writeup</a> on EQ'Lizer</li>
<li><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=109">Coldain Rings Part 1</a> - Monkly Business</li>
<li><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=108">Coldain Rings Part 2</a> - Monkly Business</li>
<li><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=174">Coldain Ring # 10 - Part 1</a> - Monkly Business</li>
<li><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=173">Coldain Ring # 10 - Part 2</a> - Monkly Business</li>
<li><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=172">Coldain Rings # 10 - Part 3</a> - Monkly Business</li>

</ul>
</p> 
<p>
Ring 1: <b>Copper Coldain Insignia Ring</b>: +1 AC, +1 Str, +1 Save vs Magic, All/All
</p>
<p>
Garadain Glacierbane, a dwarf in the huts northeast of the Ry'gorr fort, is looking for a blanket to keep him warm. In return for this blanket you receive the Copper Coldain Ring. The blanket is made by combining 4 pelts in a tailoring kit:
</p>
<table border="1">
<tr><th>Item</th><th>Recipe</th><th>Trivial</th></tr>
<tr>
<td class="intable"><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=5293&menustr=">Coldain Hunting Blanket</a></td><td class="intable">Components: <a href="/items/show_item.php?item=1357">high quality cougarskin</a>(2), <a href="/items/show_item.php?item=1359">high quality tundra kodiak pelt</a>(2)<br />In: <a href="/items/show_item.php?item=1427">small sewing kit</a>, <a href="/items/show_item.php?item=1614">deluxe sewing kit</a>, <a href="/items/show_item.php?item=1733">large sewing kit</a>, <a href="/items/show_item.php?item=1791">loom</a>, <a href="/items/show_item.php?item=5228">planar sewing kit</a>, <a href="/items/show_item.php?item=7340">collapsible sewing kit</a><br />Notes: Previously reported Trivial 41. Another report of Trivial at 44. Definitely Conflicting Information.</td><td align="center" class="intable">&lt;=76</td>
</tr>
</table>

<p>
Tundra Kodiaks in the Eastern Wastes drop the High Quality Tundra Kodiak Pelts. Snow Cougars in the Eastern Wastes and Iceclad Ocean drop the High Quality Snow Cougar Pelts.
</p> 
<p>
Ring 3: <b>Gold Coldain Insignia Ring</b>: +3 AC, +3 Str, +3 Save vs Magic, All/All
</p>
<p>
Garadain Glacierbane, a dwarf in the huts northeast of the Ry'gorr fort, is looking for a hunting knife. This is made by combining a Skinning Rock, a High Quality Walrus Hide, and a Wooly Rhino Horn in a forge. This produces a tradeable Hunting Knife. This is trivial at a smithing skill of 41.
</p> 
<p>
Walruses in the Eastern Wastes drop the High Quality Walrus Hides. Wooly Rhinos in the Eastern Wastes drop the Wooly Rhino Horn. Skinning rocks are found in the Eastern Wastes as ground spawns, they look like a rough black rock on the ground and an egg shape in inventory. Skinning rocks are no drop
</p>
<p>
Ring 4: <b>Platinum Coldain Insignia Ring</b>: +4 AC, +4 Str, +4 Save vs Magic, All/All
</p>
<p>This portion of the quest requires no tradeskilling... but the Coldain Smithy Hammer is needed in the Planes of Power, Aid Grimel Quest (Part 3 Jewelcraft) to make the <b><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=9483&menustr=">Pure Enchanted Velium Bar</a></b>. True, this portion of the quest does require you to turn in the Hammer, but nothing prevents you from completing this step twice... once for the ring, and once for the hammer.
</p>
<p>Essentially you find Tain Hammerfrost in Eastern Wastes, (near the Iceclad bridge), talk to him... and then deal with the 4 Giants that spawn and try and kill him. One is <b>Ghrek Squatnot</b> who has a vial that Tain needs. Kill Ghrek, get the vial, give vial to Tain and get the Coldain Smithy Hammer. Turning the Hammer and Ring 3 into Garadain gets you Ring 4.
</p>
<p>
Ring 9: <b>Coldain Hero's Insignia Ring</b>: +9 AC, +9 Str, +9 Sta, +9 Save vs Magic, +50 HP, Effect: Shield of the Eighth (Right-clickable and stackable 8 point damage shield)
</p>
<p>
Need to make <i>Tainted Avalance Ale</i>
</p>
<p>
(Making this recipe is only step 3 of several steps to acquire this ring). <i>Write-up to come</i>
</p>
